The National leader of All Progressives Congress (APC) Asiwaju Bola Tinubu has mourned the sudden and unexpected passing away of Sen Bayo Osinowo, saying his loyalty and enthusiasm were legendary. Tinubu, in his condolence message to the family and Lagos State, said he was deeply hurt like other Lagosians. The former Lagos State governor said, “He was more than a close friend and political associate. Over the years, he became like a family member and brother in so many ways.” “Bayo and I have come a long way, dating back to our days in the pro-democracy struggle. We both enlisted in the Social Democratic Party (SDP) BY where he served so well as the Youth chairman of that party during the Third Republic and later in the Alliance for Democracy in 1998 after the restoration of democracy”. “Bayo’s contributions to the return of democracy were significant and enduring. As a prominent political figure in Lagos, he served our state with dedication, passion and concern for the common man. In the Lagos State House of Assembly where he was a four-time member from 2003 to 2019 representing Kosofe Constituency 1, he was more than a member of that House. He provided good leadership. “ According to him, the late Senator was a stabilising figure who worked hard and tirelessly to make Lagos a better place.